refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
mixedarray_reduce arrayarray callablecallback mixedinitial&null;
array_reduce applies iteratively the callback function to the elements of the array, so as to reduce the array to a single value.

&reftitle.returnvalues;
Returns the resulting value.
If the array is empty and initial is not passed, array_reduce returns &null;.

  &reftitle.examples;



    array_reduce example


<?php
function sum($carry, $item)
{
    $carry += $item;
    return $carry;
}

function product($carry, $item)
{
    $carry *= $item;
    return $carry;
}

$a = array(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);
$x = array();

var_dump(array_reduce($a, "sum")); // int(15)
var_dump(array_reduce($a, "product", 10)); // int(1200), because: 10*1*2*3*4*5
var_dump(array_reduce($x, "sum", "No data to reduce")); // string(17) "No data to reduce"
?>
